<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/amanda-milling> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Dame Amanda Milling was Government Whip (Lord Commissioner of HM Treasury) from 14 November 2023 to 5 July 2024. She was previously Minister for Asia at the Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office from 16 September 2021 to 7 September 2022, and Minister for Asia and the Middle East from February 2022 to 7 September 2022. Amanda read Economics and Statistics at University College London, graduating in 1997. Before becoming a Member of Parliament, Amanda worked in market research, specialising in the financial services sector. Amanda was previously Co-Chairman of the Conservative Party and Minister without Portfolio at the Cabinet Office from 13 February 2020 to 15 September 2021. She also served as Treasurer of HM Household (Deputy Chief Whip) from 28 July 2019 to 13 February 2020 and Assistant Government Whip from January 2018 to July 2019. Amanda was the Conservative MP for Cannock Chase from 2015 to 2024. Amanda sat on the Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy Committee, Education, Skills and the Economy Sub-Committee before joining the Government. Amanda was born in Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, close to the Cannock Chase constituency she represented."@en .
